## ⚙️ Setup Instructions

1. Clone the repository

```
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd finance-dashboard-backend
```

2. Create virtual environment

```
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate   (Windows)
```

3. Install dependencies

```
pip install flask flask_sqlalchemy
```

4. Run the server

```
python app.py
```

The Server will start at:

```
http://127.0.0.1:5000/
```

---

##  API Testing (IMPORTANT)

Use tools like:

* Thunder Client (VS Code)
* Postman

⚠️ Browser will NOT work (headers required)

---

##  Required Headers

Every request must include:

```
User-Id: <user_id>
Content-Type: application/json
```

## Sample Request

POST /records

Headers:
```
User-Id: 2
Content-Type: application/json

```json
{
  "amount": 3000,
  "type": "income",
  "category": "salary",
  "date": "2026-04-03",
  "notes": "monthly salary"
}

---

## 📌 API Endpoints

### 👤 Users

| Method | Endpoint    | Description        |
| ------ | ----------- | ------------------ |
| POST   | /users      | Create user        |
| GET    | /users      | Get all users      |
| PATCH  | /users/<id> | Update role/status |

---

###  Records

| Method | Endpoint      | Description   |
| ------ | ------------- | ------------- |
| POST   | /records      | Create record |
| GET    | /records      | Get records   |
| PUT    | /records/<id> | Update record |
| DELETE | /records/<id> | Delete record |

---

###  Dashboard

| Method | Endpoint            | Description              |
| ------ | ------------------- | ------------------------ |
| GET    | /dashboard/summary  | Income, expense, balance |
| GET    | /dashboard/category | Category-wise totals     |
| GET    | /dashboard/recent   | Recent transactions      |

---

## 🔄 Example Workflow (Demo)

1. Create Admin user
2. Use Admin (User-Id: 2) for all actions
3. Create records
4. Fetch dashboard summary
5. Test role restrictions:

   * Analyst cannot create users ❌
   * Admin can perform all actions ✔

---

##  Design Decisions

* Used **Flask + SQLAlchemy** for simplicity and scalability
* Implemented **middleware-based RBAC**
* Followed **separation of concerns**:

  * Routes → API layer
  * Services → Business logic
  * Models → Database
* Used **header-based authentication simulation** for simplicity

---

## ⚠️ Assumptions

* Authentication is simulated using headers (`User-Id`)
* No frontend included (backend-only assignment)
* SQLite used for simplicity

---

## ⭐ Future Improvements

* JWT Authentication
* Soft delete
